Dmitry Firtash to Bid $1.4 Billion for Russia’s Minudobreniya

-- B y   D a r y n a   K r a s n o l u t s k a
-- 
2011-06-02T11:56:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-02/dmitry-firtash-to-bid-1-4-billion-for-russia-s-minudobreniya.html
Ukrainian billionaire Dmitry Firtash
will offer $1.4 billion for OAO Minudobreniya, a Russian
chemical maker, his press office said.  Firtash seeks to purchase the plant as it is located 100
kilometers from the Ukrainian-Russian border, while it can
acquire natural gas for $80 per thousand cubic meters, according
to an e-mailed statement today. The information will be
published in weekly magazine Fokus tomorrow, according to the
statement.  Ukraine’s chemical producers are paying $170 per thousand
cubic meters for Russian gas this year, Prime Minister  Mykola Azarov  said April 16.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Daryna Krasnolutska in Kiev at 
 dkrasnolutsk@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
